Why did they get rid of the naming convention!? Split cards have always had the clever “X and Y” phrase to them. Breaking and Entering, Trial and Error, Wax and Wane, Dead and Gone, Rise and Fall... 

Even the Amonkhet Aftermath cards had the “to” for their names, like Commit to Memory and Leave to Chance. 

What the hell is this “Status and Statue” business? Words that have all but one letter in common are just not enough to justify breaking that tradition.
They realized they would eventually run out of meaningful clever names.
